main event: Two objects with white, red, and orange lights were observed for ten minutes on March 31, 1966.
interesting points: One object had a combination of white, red, and orange lights, while the other had only red lights on top., Witnesses heard a whining sound during the sighting., The objects were observed close to Griffin AFB, New York., The sighting lasted for a total of ten minutes., The report concludes the objects were identified as aircraft.
